Citigroup Close to U-Turn on Private-Label Card Unit, FT Says

-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n
-- 
2011-07-14T04:53:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-14/citigroup-close-to-u-turn-on-private-label-card-unit-ft-says.html
Citigroup Inc. (C)  is close to deciding
to keep its profitable private-label credit card business after
improved market conditions prompted a rethink, the Financial
Times reported, citing people familiar with the matter.  The unit, which provides credit cards for companies such as
 Sears Holdings Corp. (SHLD)  and  Home Depot Inc. (HD) , had been marked for
sale after the financial crisis, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Peterson in London on 
 cpeterson@bloomberg.net  